Share this on WhatsAppSpread the loveMinister of Transportation, Hon. Chibuike Rotimi Amaechi, has been invested with a traditional title at Daura on Saturday.
Daura is the hometown of President Muhammadu Buhari.
Amaechi received traditional title of Dan Amanar from the Emir, Dr Umar Faruk Umar, in recognition of his contribution to the emirate.
“Daura Emirate does not give title anyhow but to people who deserve its tittle like the two we are recognising today,” the emir said.
“We’re indeed grateful to the Federal Government, political leaders, traditional as well as religious leaders from all parts of the country for honouring our invitation witness the occasion.”
Among the dignitaries who graced the occasion were the chief host, Governor Aminu Masari, Heads of MDAs and traditional leaders from all parts of the country.
